Program: Last Word
Title: Lord Ashley, Levon Helm, Wendy Grant, Charles Colson, Val May
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01ghgkc
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 29 Apr 2012
Matthew Bannister on Lord Ashley, who as the Labour MP Jack Ashley, overcame deafness to become a champion of disabled people's rights Also, Levon Helm, the drummer and singer of The Band - who backed Bob Dylan and recorded acclaimed albums of their own. Wendy Grant - the neuropathologist who came out of retirement to warn that Mad Cow Disease could affect humans Charles Colson - special counsel to Richard Nixon - who carried out dirty tricks against the President's opponents, but later found God. And Val May, the theatre director who established the reputation of the Bristol Old Vic. Show less